observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
1. Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a Schedule of Unreleased Checks at the end of each month for submission to the Office of the Municipal Accountant, and; 
2. Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare a JEV to record for the restoration of the cash equivalent to the unreleased checks and for the recognition of the appropriate payable/liability accounts. Moreover, in the ensuing year, a JEV shall be prepared to reverse the entries made covering the restoration of cash balance in the previous year.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
1. Make adjusting entries for the reversion of the unappropriated surplus Accounts Payable, Due to Officers and Employees and Due to LGUs/Due to GOCCs and Other Payables which could not be substantiated due to unavailability of data/records/documents;
2. Exert efforts to dig records as to the source agencies of the transactions under the Due to NGAs. Evaluate the same for possible return to the source agencies if these were balances of funds that have been implemented by the municipality;
3. Return to General Fund the Due to Other Funds balance;
4. Make representation with all the suppliers and contractors by preparing letters informing them of the amount due them and the required supporting documents to the claims. Likewise, we recommended that the GSO and the Municipal Engineer help in securing the required documents pertaining to the unclaimed retention money. After which, assess or evaluate such unclaimed retention money which could possibly be reverted to the unappropriated surplus;
5. Prepare a listing of the liability accounts which will be considered as miscellaneous income so as to benefit from the fund instead of keeping the same idle and unused.

The Audit Team recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
1. Instruct the Inventory Committee to prepare the inventory report using the prescribed form of the RPCPP and submit the same to the Audit Team not later than January 31 of each year, hence reported properties of the Municipality could be properly verified as to existence, valuation, rights/ownership would be substantiated.
2. Request the PGIS the record of the donated property, if the same could not be provided, create an appraisal committee to appraise the power generator, hence the Municipal Accountant will have a basis for recording the generator in the books of the Municipality;
3. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to record the donated power generator in the books of accounts;
4. Instruct the Supply Officer to locate records of the demolished properties and submit to the Accounting Office as basis in the derecognition of the properties from the books; and,
5. Instruct the Supply Officer to prepare IIRUP and take picture of the unserviceable and destroyed properties and submit a request for inspection together with pictures of the items to the Audit Team. After which, the Audit Team together with the Disposal Committee will inspect, validate and sign the IIRUP, then furnish a copy to the Accounting Office and Supply Officer as their basis in the derecognition of the unserviceable properties from the books and the PPE reports, respectively, thus both the RPCPPE and PPE accounts in the FS are adjusted.

