We have recommended that the concerned employees of the Municipality see to it that the provisions of The 2016 Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 are strictly adhered to promote transparency, accountability, equity, efficiency and economy in the procurement process.
We have further recommended that:
The Bids and Awards Committee ensure that they invite observers who do not have direct or indirect interest on the contract to be bid;
The ICO-Municipal Accountant withhold retention money or require a special bank guarantee for the procurement of goods to warrant repair on any manufacturing defects;
The Municipal Mayor approve prepared design plans and specifications that would best fit the needs and objectives of the Municipality to avoid unnecessary work suspensions and approve variation orders only that are justified, necessary and for the best interest of the Municipality and its constituents;
The Municipal Engineer undertake detailed engineering activities before the bidding process. Furthermore, he should facilitate the immediate completion of the project Improvement of Multi-Purpose Hall at Belen Day Care Center to enable the constituents of the Municipal Government to enjoy the benefits they could derive from the said project; and
The Bids and Awards Committee see to it that the timelines for the procurement process are strictly observed to avoid unnecessary delays in the implementation of projects.
